        title Timestamp Microservice
    
    body
        div(class="container")
            h1(class="header") API Basejump: Timestamp Microservice
        
            p By: Sunny Thodupunuri | 
                a(href="https://github.com/sthodup1/timestamp_microservice", target="_blank") Github Repo
            
            blockquote User stories:
                ul 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
                ul 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.</ul>
                ul 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.</ul>
                
            h3 Example usage:
            code 
                a(style="color:inherit", href="/December%2015,%202015", target="_blank") https://timestamp-api-microservice.herokuapp.com/December%2015,%202015
            br
            code 
                a(style="color:inherit" href="/1450137600",target="_blank") https:/timestamp-api-microservice.herokuapp.com/1450137600
            h3 Example output:
            code.
                {
                  "unix": 1450137600,
                  "natural": "December 15, 2015"
                }